//converts the table data types from string to int and float where necessary aka mileage, manufacture_year and price_eur
import org.apache.spark.sql.types.FloatType
import org.apache.spark.sql.types.IntegerType
val cardata2 = carDataRaw.select ("maker", "model","mileage","manufacture_year", "fuel_type", "price_eur")
val cardata3= cardata2.withColumn("mileage_int", cardata2("mileage").cast(IntegerType)).drop("mileage").withColumnRenamed("mileage_int","mileage")
val cardata4= cardata3.withColumn("manufacture_int", cardata2("manufacture_year").cast(IntegerType)).drop("manufacture_year").withColumnRenamed("manufacture_int","manufacture_year")
val carDataUse= cardata4.withColumn("price_float", cardata2("price_eur").cast(FloatType)).drop("price_eur").withColumnRenamed("price_float","price_eur")
